The paper deals with the problem of automating the annotation of whole slide images of tumor biopsies, which involves segmenting and annotating different tissue compartments based on multiple stains. This is a computer vision problem that involves deep learning techniques, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel one-shot color deconvolution deep learning method, which suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the need for correlative analysis of various biomarkers, which suggests that it may belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with digitized slide images, which suggests that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
